{"lemma":"دَهْرٌ","slug":"دَهْرٌ","root":"د.ه.ر","root_slug":"د-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَهْر","root":"دهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13261"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overcome, to conquer, to subdue, to overpower, to master, to gain the mastery over, to prevail, to predominate over, to surpass"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَهَرَ (dahara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the course of time, fate","examples":[{"text":"وَقَالُوا۟ مَا هِيَ إِلَّا حَيَاتُنَا ٱلدُّنۡيَا نَمُوتُ وَنَحۡيَا وَمَا يُهۡلِكُنَاۤ إِلَّا ٱلدَّهۡرُ ۚ وَمَا لَهُم بِذَ ٰ⁠لِكَ مِنۡ عِلۡمٍ ۖ إِنۡ هُمۡ إِلَّا يَظُنُّونَ"},{"text":"هَلْ أَتَىٰ عَلَى الْإِنْسَانِ حِينٌ مِنَ الدَّهْرِ لَمْ يَكُن شَيْئًا مَّذْكُورًا"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/da.ha.ra/","/dahr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13261","headword_ar":"دَهْرٌ","root":"dhr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daharN","text_ar":"دَهَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the latter either a dial. var., agreeably with the opinion of the Basrees in cases of this kind, and therefore such cases are limited by the authority of hearsay, or it is so written and pronounced because of the guttural letter, and so is accordant to a universal rule, agreeably with the opinion of the Koofees, (ISd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time, from the beginning of the world to its end;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Esh-Sháfi'ee, Az, Msb, Er-Rághib;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiynN","text_ar":"حِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Esh-Sháfi'ee, Az:) this is the primary signification: (Er-Rághib:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any long period of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, Mgh, K, Er-Rághib;) thus differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnN","text_ar":"زَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which will be explained below: (Er-Rághib:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of the longest period of time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (S, A,) or signifies also, (Az, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnN","text_ar":"زَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, Az, S, A, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether long or short:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or this is the proper signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnN","text_ar":"زَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but not of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a division of the year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a less period:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb:) Az says, I have heard more than one of the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqamonaA EalaY maA='i ka*aA dahorFA","text_ar":"اَقَمْنَا عَلَى مَا=ءِ كَذَا دَهْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We stayed at such a water a long time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlmaroEaY yakofiynaA dahorFA","text_ar":"هٰذَا المَرْعَى يَكْفِينَا دَهْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This pasture-land will suffice us a long time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but one does not say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is four times, or four seasons, because its application to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a short period of time is tropical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and an extension of its proper signification: (Msb:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long unlimited time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extended indivisible space of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"duration without end; time without end"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb;) it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differs from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnN","text_ar":"زَمَانٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in having no end:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Khálid Ibn-Yezeed:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prolonged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lengthened, term;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN mamoduwdN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ مَمْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, in some copies of which, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abd","text_ar":"ابد"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amad","text_ar":"اَمَد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period, or duration, of life; an age:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 183:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"present state of existence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thousand years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adohurN","text_ar":"اَدْهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhuwrN","text_ar":"دُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, K:) both said to be pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and no other pls. are known as those of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daharN","text_ar":"دَهَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adohaArN","text_ar":"اَدْهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"not having been heard. (TA.) ―         -b2-  You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY Ealayohi dahorN","text_ar":"مَضَى عَلَيْهِ دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhuwrN","text_ar":"دُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long time"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an age"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ages,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed over him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`lika","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahora Aln~ajomi","text_ar":"دَهْرَ النَّجْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in the time"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God's creation"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the stars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the beginning of time; in ancient time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^aw~ali Ald~ahori","text_ar":"فِى اَوَّلِ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the beginning of time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaboqaY Ald~ahora","text_ar":"يَبْقَى الدَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It remains for ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A=tiyhi Ald~ahora","text_ar":"لَا ا=تِيهِ الدَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to him, ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhirN","text_ar":"دَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAma","text_ar":"صَامَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahora","text_ar":"الدَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fasted ever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"always"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Awl","text_ar":"اول"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c. [See a trad. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=la","text_ar":"ا=لَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in that art.]) ―         -b8-  [Hence, because, in one sense, time brings to pass events, good and evil,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was applied by the Arabs to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and they used to blame and revile it: and as the doing so was virtually blaming and reviling God, since events are really brought to pass by Him, Mohammad forbade their doing thus. (Az, Mgh, TA, &c.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tasub~uwA A@ld~ahora","text_ar":"لَا تَسُبُّوا ا@لدَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~a A@ld~ahora huwa A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّ ا@لدَّهْرَ هُوَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, TA, &c.,) or, accord. to one reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~a A@ll~`hu huwa A@ld~ahoru","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّ ا@للّٰهُ هُوَ ا@لدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Mgh, TA, &c.,) in which some explain"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aldhr","text_ar":"الدهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first proposition as having a different meaning from that which it has in the second, whereas others assign to it the same meaning in both cases: (TA:) the meaning of the trad. is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Revile ye not"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Efficient of fortune; for the Efficient of fortune is God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, TA, &c.:) or, accord. to the second reading,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for God is the Efficient of fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence, (TA,) some reckon"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the names of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, &c.:) but some disallow this: and some say that it is allowable if meant to signify, as rendered above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Efficient of fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, &c.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawoju dahorK","text_ar":"زَوْجُ دَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A husband prepared for the accidents or calamities of fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bhr","text_ar":"بهر"},{"kind":"text","text":". [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahorN","text_ar":"بَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An evil event"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accident; a misfortune; a calamity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahaAriyru","text_ar":"دَهَارِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [And see 1.] ―         -b11-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A purpose; an intention:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a desire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end that one has in view."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA dahoriY","text_ar":"مَا دَهْرِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA dahoriY ka*aA","text_ar":"مَا دَهْرِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My purpose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my scope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the end that I have in view,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is not such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b12-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is constant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 183,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that lasts throughout life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA *aAka bidahoriY","text_ar":"مَا ذَاكَ بِدَهْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is not my custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that lasts throughout my life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA dahoriY bika*aA","text_ar":"مَا دَهْرِى بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My habit throughout life is not so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","ISd","Az","S","A","Msb","Sh","Mgh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}